    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The `rangeSlider` widget reacts to `numericRefinements`. Here's an example with the `price` attribute:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  indexName: 'instant_search',\r\n  searchClient,\r\n  searchParameters: {\r\n    numericRefinements: {\r\n      price: {\r\n        '>=': [15],\r\n        '<=': [115],\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that in the upcoming InstantSearch v4, this will be more straightforward with the concept of `uiState`:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// Available from InstantSearch v4\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  indexName: 'instant_search',\r\n  searchClient,\r\n  initialUiState: {\r\n    range: {\r\n      price: '15:115',\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n```",
